description: From Latin abstrūdō (“push away, hide”). See abstruse.

verbs.description: abstrude (third-person singular simple present abstrudes, present participle abstruding, simple past and past participle abstruded)

examples: In winter, owing to the great amount of water poured into the sea, and the less amount abstruded by evaporation, the water stands some ten or twelve feet higher than at other times.
